    <stitle>NEWAY AIR SUSPENSION - ALIGNMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0300204" svcproctype="align" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ALIGNMENT</title>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>When welding alignment bushing or tightening bushing or torque rod fasteners to specifications,
                    the vehicle must be at proper ride height to avoid introducing unnecessary stress on the bushings
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <para>Refer to GROUP 03, SUSPENSION ALIGNMENT for axle alignment procedure. Specific alignment adjustment can be
            made by shimming the torque rods and using the alignment bushings shown in
            <hotlnk document="s03002r_8.xml" xrefid="f0300211">Figure 11</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk document="s03002r_8.xml" xrefid="f0300212">Figure 12</hotlnk>, Item 17. For welding, refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300219">Figure 19</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0300219" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0300219" filename="../figg03/g0300219.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 19. WELDING ALIGNMENT BUSHING</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.1/2 INCH (13MM) AXLE ALIGNMENT BOTH SIDES OF EACH FRAME BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>PROVIDES 2 INCHES (51MM) TOTAL ALIGNMENT AT AXLE TRACK.</callout1>
                <callout1>2.POSITION WELD OR USE "VERTICAL UP" WELDS 3 PLACES -1 INCH (25MM) WELDS- AS SHOWN. BOTH SIDES
                    OF FRAME BRACKET AFTER AXLE IS ALIGNED WITH FRAME AT SPECIFIED RIDE HEIGHT.
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
